texts.text: >You continue to explore the school that is now a maze.
Hey, you said you were looking for missing people too, right?
How many are still missing?
Around 10 people if you count the teachers.
Hey look! Somebody's lying over there!
Speak of the devil! Here's missing person number one...!
Fuyuki?!
>Seeing Fuyuki lying face down in the middle of the corridor, Haru runs to him.
Hey wait!
Stop! We don't know if that's really Fuyuki...
It doesn't matter! I have to save Fuyuki!
You okay with that, Shiva?
Shit! Come back Haru! Don't be so hasty!
Fuyuki! You okay? C'mon, wake up! Fuyuki!
*Murmur*
>Clutched in Haru's arms, Fuyuki slowly opens his eyes.
H-Haru...?
Fuyuki!?! It's really you!
It's really Fuyuki? That was unexpected.

Hehehe.
You're so silly Haru.
>Fuyuki chuckles, then...
You still can't tell the difference.
>tries to stab Haru in the throat with a knifehand.
>But Shiva stops him just in time.
You saw through my guise.
Even in this dimension, your power still remain.
I do not need the full extent of my power to see through your tricks,
Angra Mainyu.
Hehehe...
Of course, I never expected to succeed in slaying the host of one as great as you like that.
After all, I am not yet fully restored.
Then I shall vanquish you here and now, even if I have to kill your host in the process!
What?! Shiva!
>Manifesting his Trishula (trident) into existence, Shiva lunges at Fuyuki with Haru's body.
No, I can't have that.
>But Angra Mainyu stops it with his fingertip.
Tsk...
What a cruel thing to do, making one friend kill another.
It is but a small thing compared to stopping your return.
No... Shiva...

Poor Haru...
But you need not worry.
Fuyuki will not die. He cannot die.
What do you mean...?
The darkness that resides in this boy's heart, the evil thoughts brewing inside its deepest depths...
It is very cozy. The most soothing cradle.
Therefor I will protect him myself, until I am fully restored.
This boy will become the foundation of my resurrection in a short while.
For now, I will withdraw. But we shall meet again.
Halt!
>Disregarding Shiva's order,
>Angra Mainyu and Fuyuki disappear into the shadows...

The darkness inside Fuyuki...?
No. I don't...
It... Doesn't matter! I have to find Fuyuki!
Just hold it Haru! Stop!
>All of you retrain Haru, who is trying to run off without you again.
That's right Haru!
You almost got killed back there, remember?!
B-But Fuyuki...
I know he's your close friend, but there's no need to risk your life...
Fuyuki's more than just a friend to me!
We were together ever since we were babies.
And above all, he's my hero.
Your hero?
Yes.
One day, when we were on a trip to the countryside, we encountered a snake at a local shrine.
When it attacked, Fuyuki shielded me from it and got bit,
But he still smiled at me, even when he was in a fever from the venom...
So I aspired to be his hero too.
It's what I've been striving for in life...
To be a hero, only for him.
But these days, just being with him causes people to interfere...
I try to brush it off, but I'm afraid of causing trouble for Fuyuki...
But even so, I want to be with Fuyuki! So I can't wait. I have to find him as quickly as...
You really care for Fuyuki a lot, don't you Haru?
More than the word "friend" can describe.
A-Aghh...
>Haru is about to reply, when a strange voice rings out near him.
What the hell was that disgusting sound...? Meat Balloon...
It wasn't me!
I meant to ask you whether you heard it too.

Oh, right...
Ahem!
Yeah, I did hear something odd. From this classroom maybe?
>Gakuto points at the classroom right beside where Fuyuki lay in the hallway.
C-C-Cold... Brrr...
>A faint but distinct groaning can be heard coming from it.
A demon maybe?
I don't know, but...
Let's take it out. Better be safe than sorry!
>Gakuto kicks open the door.
>You find a terrified man inside.
Wait, he's a teacher!
One of the missing people?
Yes.
He must've taken refuge here. I'm so relieved to find him.
Wait Haru, something's wrong with him.
He's just a bit shook up, which is normal since he's been hiding here alone all this time.
C'mon, let's get you somewhere...
>Haru takes the teacher's hand to pull him up.
Whoa! That burns!
>The teacher doesn't respond. He shudders for a moment...
>Then falls forward to the ground, breaking into a million tiny pieces on impact.
What?
Don't look!
>Gakuto cuts in to shield everyone else from the sight.
>Then frosty cold air comes pouring in from the side of the classroom where the teacher was!

Shit...!
Everyone out! Now!
But the teacher...
Now! Or we'll all die!

*Pant*
Is everyone... Alright?
I-I think so... Whoa! Meat Balloon! You're back! It's frozen!
Oh, that. No problem, I'll survive.
Good thing we got outta there in time though. That was close.
Yo Shiva, was that...?
Yes, that was Winter, another one of Angra Mainyu's scourges.
That's what I thought.
Why do this? It's like he's pulling them out of his hat one by one.
I do not understand his motive either.
>His eyes closed, Siva looks troubled.
Let us make haste, lest he grows stronger.
We have to do this deed, even if we have to take that boy's life as well.
